  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Palau Emergency Preparedness and Enhanced Resilience (PEPER)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">While the Republic of Palau&apos;s urban center and remote islands have unique challenges, the island nation is among the most vulnerable to the adverse effects of natural disasters and hazards including typhoons, floods, droughts, and tsunamis. Disaster risk reduction (DRR) activities are therefore critical to help communities and governments reduce risks, lessen the impact of disasters, and build resilience. The project contributes to the Republic of Palau&apos;s preparedness and ability to respond to hazard events by strengthening evacuation shelters, training community leaders on shelter management, testing pre-disaster government response structures in tabletop exercises, and pre-positioning relief items.</narrative>
  </description>
